## **Initiate**
_Each ability costs 1 talent point_

**Abilities**:
- **Gale Force Strike:** When you hit a creature of your size or smaller, or any creature one size category larger than you, with a weapon, you can create a gust of wind that forces the creature to make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is pushed 10 feet away from you. The distance increases by an additional 10 feet at 5th Adept level (20 feet), 9th Master level (30 feet), 13th Grandmaster level (40 feet), and 17th Great-grandmaster level (50 feet). This effect can be used once per turn.
- **Misty Escape:** When you take damage, you can use your reaction to turn into a cloud of mist, causing the attack to miss. You must spend a spell slot of 1st level or higher to use this ability. 
- **Mistbound Step:** The Misty Step spell does not consume a spell slot if you begin or end your movement in a heavily obscured area.
- **Misty Veil:** You can create a shroud of mist around you that obscures your appearance, granting advantage on Stealth checks to hide and disadvantage on Insight checks to discern your true intentions. This effect lasts for 1 hour and can be used once per long rest.
- **Wind Sprint:** You can double your movement speed for 1 minute. You must spend a short or long rest to use this ability again.
- **Thunderous Roar:** You can let out a powerful roar that creates a shockwave, forcing all creatures within 10 feet to make a Constitution saving throw or be pushed 10 feet away from you and become deafened for 1 minute. This ability can be used once per short or long rest.
- **Sound Analysis:** You can accurately determine the source and direction of any sound within 300 feet of you. This ability can be used to track creatures or detect hidden enemies. It provides you advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks related to sound.

